---
import WizardTab from "components/partials/wizard_tab.astro";
import Ec from "snippets/ec.astro";
---

<div class="mt" style="--mt: 10">
  <WizardTab />

  <ul class="wizard uk-switcher mt-2">
    <li class="uk-active">
      <div class="mt" style="--mt: 10"></div>

      <p class="uk-paragraph">
        To include the Chart library via CDN, add the following to your HTML <code
          class="uk-codespan">&lt;head&gt;</code
        >:
      </p>

      <Ec project="kit" path="installation.chart" />
    </li>
    <li>
      <div class="mt" style="--mt: 10"></div>

      <p class="uk-paragraph">
        If you're building a modern app with a bundler, you can import the
        JavaScript file from <code class="uk-codespan">franken-ui</code> into your
        <code class="uk-codespan">app.js</code> file.
      </p>

      <Ec project="kit" path="chart_introduction.1" />

      <h2 class="uk-h3 mt" style="--mt: 10">CSS</h2>

      <p class="uk-paragraph">To include the necessary CSS:</p>

      <Ec project="kit" path="chart_introduction.3" />
    </li>
  </ul>
</div>
